init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Information, provided people actually take the time to learn from it, is terribly empowering.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If we don't, we aren't truly participating in the democratic process.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The recent election in the US taught us that it's difficult to determine what information is really true and what's just one person's opinion.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is complicated even more when you add in all of the texts, tweets, e-mails, and facebook feeds that fill up a person's news

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Even if people try to stay up-to-date, the sheer amount of news out there seems to be overwhelming.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In this day and age, news organizations are trying to fill the voids left behind by decline of investigative journalism.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This has left many people in the US without the ability to critically think about the world they live in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If we actively seek out the truth, but hold on to our skepticism, it doesn't matter if we don't catch every piece of news.
